<title>INDIA: Bausch and Lomb 96/97 net 5.18 mln rupees.</title>
<headline>Bausch and Lomb 96/97 net 5.18 mln rupees.</headline>
<dateline>NEW DELHI 1997-08-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bausch and Lomb India Ltd (BLIL) declared  a net profit of 5.18 million rupees for 1996/97 (April-March) on Friday,  the United News of India (UNI) said. </p>
<p>The news agency said this was the first time that BLIL, a unit of  Bausch and Lomb Inc, had declared a profit. BLIL started operations  in 1992.</p>
<p>It quoted the company's chairman Paul Ruddlesdin saying the annual  sales figure included exports of eyewear and vision care products  to Europe and neighbouring countries.</p>
